column82: I think it is a reflection of their cultural background and shows being influenced heavily by both cultures the languages belong to. Usually I assume a person has very recent ties to the country of their ancestry and family members that primarily speak in the mother language. I find it very comforting and familiar when others speak Spanglish, but I am aware that there is a negative perception of it by others who consider it to be tacky or ignorant. To reiterate, to me it just shows simultaneously living amongst dual environments and cultures.
